# statica site authoring

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/guide.md](../../docs/guide.md). Copy patterns from [examples/blog/](../../examples/blog/).

## Core rules

- HTML-first — no React/Vue/JSX. Valid HTML + statica attributes.
- Routing: `**/index.html`; dynamic segments use `[slug]`, `[page]`, `[locale]` folders.
- Fragments: three-part `id` contract — `<link rel="statica/fragment">`, `<slot id="…">`, `<template id="…">`.
- Text content → `<slot name="field">`. Attributes → `${field}`. Every field must be in `data-bind`.
- Collection: `<html data-bind="arrayId">` + funnel script. Pagination: `data-bind="items"` + `[[pagination]]` in TOML.
- Paths relative to the declaring HTML file. Aliases via `@Name/tail` from `statica.toml`.
- Always lowercase **statica**.

## Anti-patterns

- `${field}` in text nodes (use slots)
- `<slot>` inside attributes
- Undeclared `${…}` bindings
- `[page]` and `[slug]` in the same route tree
- Runtime fetch for static content

Verify with `statica build` or `statica watch`.
